PMID== 2283713
TI  == [a clinical evaluation of cefdinir in pediatric infections].
AB  == cefdinir (cfdn), a new oral cephalosporin, was administered to 10 patients with various infections and the following results were obtained. 1. clinical responses in 10 patients (1 patient with rhinitis, 2 with sinusitis, 1 with pharyngitis, 1  with tonsillitis, 4 with scarlet fever and 1 with abscess) were excellent in 6 and good in 4 with an efficacy rate of 100%. 2. eleven species of bacteria were isolated (3 of staphylococcus aureus, 6 of streptococcus pyogenes and 2 of haemophilus influenzae) and all of them were eradicated by the treatment with cfdn. 3. no side effects or abnormal laboratory test values were noted. none of the patients refused to take the drug.
TIHT== 
