AB  == the in vitro activity of spiramycin and erythromycin has been determined by an agar diffusion method against relevant clinical isolates. generally, erythromycin was more active than spiramycin on a weight-for-weight basis. spiramycin showed only moderate activity against haemophilus influenzae and streptococcus pyogenes. gonococci were sensitive in vitro to both agents. many erythromycin-resistant staphylococci were sensitive to spiramycin.
